### 6.

1\. Now at that time the Bhikkhus who were sick had need of fruits as
medicine.

They told this thing to the Blessed One.

'I allow you, O Bhikkhus, the use of fruits as medicine--the
vi*l*aṅga <span id="fr_98"></span>[5](#fn_96.md), the pippala <span
id="fr_99"></span>[6](#fn_97.md), and mari*k*a peppers; the harîtaka <span
id="fr_100"></span>[7](#fn_98.md), and vibhîtaka <span
id="fr_101"></span>[8](#fn_99.md), and âmalaka <span
id="fr_102"></span>[9](#fn_100.md) myrobalans; the go*th*a fruit <span
id="fr_103"></span>[10](#fn_101.md); and whatsoever other fruits are used
for medicine, and impart an appetising flavour to foods, either hard or
soft, which the

<span id="page_47">p. 47</span>

sick Bhikkhus could not otherwise eat. They may be received and stored
up (&c., as in chap. 4, down to:) guilty of a dukka*t*a offence,'

